{"ts":"2026-07-17T04:41:29.345Z","author":"maintainer-agent","op":"create","patch":[{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/id","value":"pm-bu1m"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/title","value":"GH-576: pm <unknown-command> --help exits 0 with root help instead of unknown-command error — false positive for agent capability probes"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/description","value":"pm badcmd fails correctly (non-zero, suggestions), but pm badcmd --help prints ROOT help and exits 0 — the -h/--help interception layer short-circuits unknown-command detection. Probing 'pm <cmd> --help' is the canonical way agents check whether a subcommand exists and learn its contract, so this returns a false positive: the agent concludes the command exists, misreads root help as the command's options, and burns turns on the eventual error. Same interception-layer class as pm-albl (contract layer intercepts -h/--help before variadic-positional handlers); distinct from GH-490/pm-g543 (suggestion ranking). Fix: unknown-command detection must run before (or inside) help interception — pm <unknown> --help should behave like pm <unknown>: non-zero exit, 'Unknown command <name>', did-you-mean suggestions."},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/type","value":"Issue"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/status","value":"open"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/priority","value":2},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/tags","value":["agent-ux","area:cli","defect-class"]},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/created_at","value":"2026-07-17T04:41:29.345Z"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/updated_at","value":"2026-07-17T04:41:29.345Z"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/author","value":"maintainer-agent"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/estimated_minutes","value":180},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/acceptance_criteria","value":"pm <unknown> --help exits non-zero with the unknown-command error and suggestions (parity with pm <unknown>); known-command --help behavior unchanged; regression spec covers both the arbitrary-name and plausible-name (e.g. pm link --help) cases; GH-576 closed with evidence"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/parent","value":"pm-mpbb"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/risk","value":"low"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/confidence","value":"high"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/dependencies","value":[{"id":"pm-2tan","kind":"related","created_at":"2026-07-17T04:41:29.345Z"},{"id":"pm-albl","kind":"related","created_at":"2026-07-17T04:41:29.345Z"},{"id":"pm-g543","kind":"related","created_at":"2026-07-17T04:41:29.345Z"},{"id":"pm-gdi7","kind":"related","created_at":"2026-07-17T04:41:29.345Z"}]}],"before_hash":"3cc22dff72be7b14824654a7a64ea62b04799939b2fee54c1b5f52ca60bf6df0","after_hash":"604b6a216ddb7d142c40790b7cbaac3986bfbee3890a4e0070a6daaf0bf7f4cf","message":""}
